docs.lead_paragraph: MIDWEST," U.S.A. AT 7:06 o'clock of a spring morning not long ago a 7-year-old boy was awakened by his mother, stirred in his bed, whimpered, kicked his feet rapidly is protest at the idea of getting up, squirmed around and rolled over.
